🟢 Open
The port is actively accepting connections and a service is running on it (e.g., HTTP on port 80).

🔴 Closed
The port is reachable, but no service is listening on it.

🚫 Filtered
Nmap cannot determine whether the port is open or closed because a firewall or filter is blocking packets.

⚪ Unfiltered
The port is reachable, but Nmap cannot tell if it is open or closed (usually seen in ACK scans).

🟡 Open | Filtered
Nmap cannot distinguish whether the port is open or filtered (no response received).

🟠 Closed | Filtered
The port is either closed or filtered, but Nmap cannot confirm which one.
